{"word":"ἀλλοιόω","slug":"ἀλλοιόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀλλοιόω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀλλοῖος'><el>ἀλλοῖος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to make different, to change, alter</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> with <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>mid.</a> <el>ἀλλοιώσομαι</el> and <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <el>ἀλλοιωθήσομαι</el>:—<i>to become different, be changed</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to be changed for the worse</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b> Hence<p/></div>"}]}